  <user-story>
    <as-a>maker</as-a>
    <i-want>to make updates to published stories and rollback changes if needed</i-want>
    <so-that>I can improve content while maintaining publication history</so-that>
  </user-story>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion id="ac1">Maker can edit published story content (text, images, process timeline, materials) without unpublishing, with edit mode clearly distinguished from view mode.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac2">**BUSINESS CRITICAL**: Each edit creates a new version with timestamp, changes log, and full content snapshot, ensuring complete version history for audit and rollback.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac3">Maker can preview changes before publishing updates with side-by-side comparison of current and modified versions.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac4">Maker can rollback to any previous version with one-click restoration and automatic version increment upon rollback.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac5">Version history is visible with change summaries, timestamps, edit reasons, and visual diff highlighting of modifications between versions.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac6">**BUSINESS CRITICAL**: Active offers and auctions are preserved during content updates with offer references locked to original version to prevent bait-and-switch.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
